18/03/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- About 1,000 people gathered in Zagreb on Thursday (March 17th) to call for the government's resignation, tossing eggs at the headquarters of the ruling Croatian Democratic Union. 
Organiser Ivan Pernar was briefly detained at the end of the demonstration. 
Another anti-government protest is scheduled for Saturday. 
(Nova TV, Vecernji List, tportal.hr - 17/03/11)
